Phrases.frases: Your focus determines your reality.

Secrets must be exposed when found. Detours must be taken when encountered. And if you are the one who stands at the crossroads or the place of concealment, you must never leave it to another to act in your place.
Life does not treat you fairly or unfairly, it merely is. It is up to each of us to be fair, or unfair.
You've been a good apprentice, Obi-Wan, and you're a much wiser man than I am. I foresee you will become a great Jedi Knight.

Yes, a Jedi’s strength flows from the Force. But beware of the dark side. Anger, fear, aggression; the dark side of the Force are they. Easily they flow, quick to join you in a fight. If once you start down the dark path, forever will it dominate your destiny, consume you it will, as it did Obi-Wan’s apprentice.
You will know (the good from the bad) when you are calm, at peace. Passive. A Jedi uses the Force for knowledge and defense, never for attack.
Train yourself to let go of everything you fear to lose.
PATIENCE YOU MUST HAVE my young padawan
When gone am I, the last of the Jedi will you be. The Force runs strong in your family. Pass on what you have learned.
Always pass on what you have learned.
Do. Or do not. There is no try.
Powerful you have become, the dark side I sense in you.
Fear is the path to the dark side. Fear leads to anger; anger leads to hate; hate leads to suffering. I sense much fear in you.
In time, the suffering of your people will persuade you to see our point of view.
Never tell me the odds!

It’s the ship that made the Kessel run in less than twelve parsecs. I’ve outrun Imperial starships. Not the local bulk cruisers, mind you. I’m talking about the big Corellian ships, now. She’s fast enough for you, old man.
The Force will be with you. Always.
Well, if droids could think, there’d be none of us here, would there?
If you define yourself by your power to take life, your desire to dominate, to possess, then you have nothing.
You were my brother, Anakin. I loved you.
Why, you stuck-up, half-witted, scruffy-looking nerf herder!
Help me, Obi-Wan Kenobi. You’re my only hope.
You know, no matter how much we fought, I’ve always hated watching you leave.
I find your lack of faith disturbing.
This technological terror is nothing compared to the power of the force
I sense something. A presence I have not felt since…. (A New Hope)
No. I am your father.
You have failed me for the last time.
Just for once, let me look on you with my own eyes.
I’ll never turn to the dark side. You’ve failed, your highness. I am a Jedi, like my father before me.
Oh, my dear friend. How I’ve missed you.
[Luke:] I can’t believe it. [Yoda:] That is why you fail.
I am no Jedi.
We must keep our faith in the Republic. The day we stop believing democracy can work is the day we lose it.
The Sith took everything from me. Ripped me from my mother’s arms, murdered my brother, used me as a weapon, and then cast me aside. Abandoned me. Once, I had power — now I have nothing
Remember, my dear Obi-Wan. I’ve loved you always. I always will.
The dark side of the Force is a pathway to many abilities some consider to be unnatural.
I’m just a simple man trying to make my way in the universe.
An object cannot make you good or evil. The temptation of power, forbidden knowledge, even the desire to do good can lead some down that path. But only you can change yourself.
The garbage’ll do!
Every time I walked away from something I wanted to forget, I told myself it was for a cause that I believed in. A cause that was worth it. Without that, we’re lost.
Jyn, I’ll be there for you. Cassian said I had to.
Power! Unlimited power!
Now, young Skywalker, you will die.
What if I told you that the Republic was now under the control of a Dark Lord of the Sith?
So this is how liberty dies. With thunderous applause.
